        {"pearl": "Pain out of proportion to the visible skin findings is the SINGLE EARLIEST and MOST IMPORTANT sign of Fournier gangrene. A patient with perineal pain requiring high-dose opioids, with little visible skin change, has Fournier until proven otherwise. Do not wait for crepitus or skin necrosis to appear — by then, the patient may be in septic shock.", "LOE": "3", "pearlType": "diagnostic"},
